{"HOVE":[{"def":"To rise; to swell; to heave; to cause to swell.","pos":""}],"HOVEL":[{"def":"A large conical brick structure around which the firing kilns are grouped.","pos":""}],"HOVELER":[{"def":"One who assists in saving life and property from a wreck; a coast boatman.","pos":""}],"HOVELING":[{"def":"A method of securing a good draught in chimneys by covering the top, leaving openings in the sides, or by carrying up two of the sides higher than the other two.","pos":""}],"HOVEN":[{"def":"Affected with the disease called hoove; as, hoven cattle.","pos":""}],"HOVER":[{"def":"A cover; a shelter; a protection.","pos":""}],"HOVERER":[{"def":"A device in an incubator for protecting the young chickens and keeping them warm.","pos":""}],"HOVERINGLY":[{"def":"In a hovering manner.","pos":""}]}